Carriage of passengers from India will be suspended from From23:59 UAE LT 24th April, and for the next 10 days subject to further review, passengers travelling from or who have transited through India in the last 14 days are not allow to enter or transit Dubai. This does not apply to Nationals of the United Arab Emirates, diplomatic and official mission passport holders, Nationals of the United Arab Emirates, diplomatic and official mission passport holders must have a printed COVID-19 PCR negative certificate with QR code. Apart from this If you are travelling from India to any other country via DUBAI, you need to have a valid transit as well as Dubai Visa and get your PCR test result from any of the UAE government approved laboratory (https://screening.purehealth.ae/application)
If you are travelling from any other city in India you should you should get your PCR test result either from any of the UAE government approved laboratory 
(https://screening.purehealth.ae/application) or any ICMR approved laboratory (https://www.icmr.gov.in/).
If you are traveling in flights (FZ 7000 to 7999) to and from Jeddah then you will need Umrah visa to board flight, Please check visa details before issuance in order to avoid ADM. These are Evacuation flights, PCR Test is mandatory by Airline certified Labs for all Destinations, 
in order to avoid NO SHOW .
